From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Galileo CSM Workspace <galileo-csm@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 15:04:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] scripts: keep SeaBIOS CSM below 128 KiB

The generic SeaBIOS CSM configuration grows to a 256 KiB Csm16.bin when built
with debug level 3. LegacyBiosDxe shadows the CSM image at the top of the
0xC0000-0xFFFFF legacy region and expects BiosStart to remain above the option
ROM base at 0xC0000. A 256 KiB CSM image makes BiosStart equal to 0xC0000 and
trips the low-memory layout assertion.

Force a 128 KiB CSM output and reduce SeaBIOS debug verbosity enough to fit
without dropping USB mass storage, drive services, option ROM support, or the
legacy boot interfaces needed for DOS.

With this configuration, the tested Csm16.bin is 131072 bytes and SeaBIOS
reported:

  Total size: 127392  Fixed: 73632  Free: 3680 (used 97.2% of 128KiB rom)

---
 scripts/build-seabios-csm.sh | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/scripts/build-seabios-csm.sh b/scripts/build-seabios-csm.sh
index f5eb053..7269913 100755
--- a/scripts/build-seabios-csm.sh
+++ b/scripts/build-seabios-csm.sh
@@ -16,7 +16,8 @@ trap 'rm -f "$tmp_config"' EXIT
 
 cat > "$tmp_config" <<'CONFIG'
 CONFIG_CSM=y
-CONFIG_DEBUG_LEVEL=3
+CONFIG_ROM_SIZE=128
+CONFIG_DEBUG_LEVEL=1
 CONFIG_DEBUG_SERIAL=y
 CONFIG_DEBUG_SERIAL_PORT=0x3f8
 CONFIG_DEBUG_COREBOOT=n
-- 
2.43.0
